benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: POST /1.0/kb/catalog/xml - Upload the full catalog as XML

covered: POST Method - Valid Payload: TC01, TC02, TC03, TC04, TC05 cover successful creations with valid payloads and varying headers.
POST Method - Invalid Payload: TC08 (malformed XML), TC09 (empty body), TC10 (unsupported content type) and TC07 (empty header value) cover invalid payload/headers scenarios.
POST Method - Duplicate Submission: TC25 covers handling of duplicate catalog version with 201 or 409 as applicable.

POST Method - Large Payloads / Boundary Conditions: TC12 (very large payload), TC27 (minimal headers with large whitespace), TC29 (different encodings), TC30 (boundary values) address payload size and boundary testing.

POST Method - Validation / Error Handling: TC08, TC09, TC10, TC16 (backend service unavailable mapped to 503), TC17 (malicious content), TC18 (corrupted XML) address input validation and error handling.
Authorization / Access Control: TC14 covers invalid authentication/authorization scenarios.
gaps: Server Error Handling (500 Internal Server Error): No explicit test simulates a 500 error (DB failure, unexpected server error).
Caching / ETag / Cache-Control: No tests verify caching headers or behavior.
Rate Limiting / Throttling: No explicit tests for rate limiting thresholds or throttling behavior beyond basic performance scenarios.

Edge/Negative Scenarios for Content-Type Rigidity: While TC10 tests invalid content type, additional coverage for other unexpected content types (e.g., multipart, missing charset) could be beneficial.
Security boundary tests: Although TC17 covers some malicious content, broader security scenarios (e.g., XXE configurations, schema evolution checks) could be more comprehensive.
recommendations: Add a test for 500 Internal Server Error to validate proper server error handling and messaging.
Add caching behavior tests (ETag/Cache-Control) to verify proper caching semantics for catalog uploads.
Add explicit rate-limiting tests (e.g., bursts, backoff behavior) to ensure system stability under load.
Expand content-type edge-case testing (e.g., missing charset, rare content types) to confirm strict API intolerance where appropriate.
Introduce a security-focused test set for XML processing (e.g., robust XXE defense, XML schema validation edge cases) beyond TC17.
